    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that it's a debate, but can you be more specific about the actual arguments? like, what's the breakdown between the originalist view and the living constitution view? i want to understand how someone would argue that the court is actually being faithful to the text vs how someone would say they're just making it up as they go.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Originalists argue that the Second Amendment's meaning must be fixed to what the Founders understood it to mean at the time of ratification, focusing on historical context to limit judicial invention. Conversely, proponents of the \"living constitution\" view argue that the amendment's meaning must evolve to address modern societal needs and technological changes. Those who claim judicial overreach argue that the modern Court ignores the original intent in favor of expansive, contemporary policy goals.",
      "source": "target",
